{"description":"Add two new tRPC procedures. Both routers already exist — just add new procedures to them.

--- PROCEDURE 1 — item.getAtRiskItems ---
FILE: src/server/api/routers/item.ts

Add to itemRouter (createTRPCRouter({...})):

  getAtRiskItems: protectedProcedure
    .query(async ({ ctx }) => {
      const userId = ctx.session.user.id;
      if (!userId) {
        throw new TRPCError({ code: 'UNAUTHORIZED' });
      }
      return ctx.db.item.findMany({
        where: {
          userId,
          status: { in: ['BAD', 'OLD', 'FRESH'] },
        },
        include: {
          itemTypes: {
            select: { id: true, name: true, suggested_life_span_seconds: true },
          },
        },
        orderBy: { status: 'asc' },
      });
    }),

NOTE: The existing getItems procedure uses a different orderBy that also sorts by status asc, but it only selects id/name/storage_advice from itemTypes. getAtRiskItems must include suggested_life_span_seconds so the client hook can run getDaysUntilExpiration (src/utils/expiration.ts) without a second round-trip. The client-side useAtRiskReview hook does the final filter to exclude FRESH items with more than 3 days remaining. Do NOT filter to <=3 days on the server — that would require computing expiry per-item in SQL, which is complex and the dataset is small enough to filter client-side.

--- PROCEDURE 2 — user.markReviewComplete ---
FILE: src/server/api/routers/user.ts

Add to userRouter (createTRPCRouter({...})):

  markReviewComplete: protectedProcedure
    .mutation(async ({ ctx }) => {
      await ctx.db.user.update({
        where: { id: ctx.session.user.id },
        data: { lastReviewedAt: new Date() },
      });
      return { success: true };
    }),

This writes lastReviewedAt = now() to the DB. The DB field is added in broccoli-dashboard-0cr (schema must be migrated before this code can run). The localStorage key 'broccoli:atRiskReview:lastCompletedDate' is set in parallel by the hook as a fast-path gate so we do not need a network round-trip on every app open — the DB field is only the cross-device source of truth.

DEPENDS ON: broccoli-dashboard-0cr (lastReviewedAt field must exist on User in schema)."}

