{"description":"Build the core draggable card component. FILE: src/components/core/AtRiskReview/AtRiskReviewCard.tsx

IMPORTS NEEDED:
  import { motion, useMotionValue, useTransform, type MotionStyle, type PanInfo } from 'framer-motion';
  import { ItemStatusType } from '@/generated/prisma/client';
  import { getItemStatusColor } from '@/components/core/ItemForm';
  import { getDaysUntilExpiration } from '@/utils/expiration';
  import type { CombinedItemType } from '@/components/core/Inventory';
  import type { ReviewDecision } from './useAtRiskReview';
  import { AtRiskReviewCardOverlay } from './AtRiskReviewCardOverlay';
  import { AtRiskReviewCardDetails } from './AtRiskReviewCardDetails';
  import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button';
  import { Utensils, Trash2, ChevronDown } from 'lucide-react';

PROPS:
  interface AtRiskReviewCardProps {
    item: CombinedItemType;
    onDecision: (decision: ReviewDecision) => void;
    style?: MotionStyle;   // scale + translateY + zIndex passed from deck for stacking
    isTop: boolean;        // only top card is draggable + shows action buttons
  }

FRAMER MOTION DRAG SETUP:
  const dragX = useMotionValue(0);
  const dragY = useMotionValue(0);
  const rotate = useTransform(dragX, [-200, 0, 200], [-15, 0, 15]);
  const SWIPE_THRESHOLD = 80;

  Drag props on the outer motion.div:
    drag={isTop ? true : false}
    dragConstraints={{ left: 0, right: 0, top: -100, bottom: 0 }}
    dragElastic={0.7}
    whileDrag={{ cursor: 'grabbing' }}
    style={{ x: dragX, y: dragY, rotate }}

  handleDragEnd(_: PointerEvent, info: PanInfo):
    - if info.offset.x > SWIPE_THRESHOLD → onDecision({ type: 'eaten' })
    - if info.offset.x < -SWIPE_THRESHOLD → onDecision({ type: 'discarded' })
    - if info.offset.y < -SWIPE_THRESHOLD → onDecision({ type: 'skipped' })
    - else → dragX.set(0); dragY.set(0);  (spring back)

  BUTTON TAP ANIMATION: When action buttons (Eaten, Discard) are tapped, animate the card off-screen first, then call onDecision in the onAnimationComplete callback:
    const controls = useAnimation();
    const handleEatenButtonClick = async () => {
      if ('vibrate' in navigator) navigator.vibrate(50);
      await controls.start({ x: 300, opacity: 0, transition: { duration: 0.3 } });
      onDecision({ type: 'eaten' });
    };
    const handleDiscardButtonClick = async () => {
      if ('vibrate' in navigator) navigator.vibrate(50);
      await controls.start({ x: -300, opacity: 0, transition: { duration: 0.3 } });
      onDecision({ type: 'discarded' });
    };
    Pass animate={controls} to the outer motion.div alongside style.

INLINE DETAIL PANEL STATE:
  const [showDetails, setShowDetails] = useState(false);
  Pass to AtRiskReviewCardDetails as open prop. Toggle via 'Update details' button.

CARD VISUAL STRUCTURE:
- Outer wrapper: motion.div with className 'rounded-2xl shadow-xl bg-white dark:bg-zinc-900 overflow-hidden w-full max-w-sm mx-auto select-none'
- Status color lookup using getItemStatusColor(item.status) from ItemForm.tsx — returns 'red-400', 'yellow-400', etc.
- Status top strip: div with className based on status:
    BAD:   'border-t-4 border-red-400 bg-red-50 dark:bg-red-950/30'
    OLD:   'border-t-4 border-yellow-400 bg-yellow-50 dark:bg-yellow-950/30'
    FRESH: 'border-t-4 border-orange-400 bg-orange-50 dark:bg-orange-950/30'
- Status badge (top-left): use CustomBadge or Badge from @/components/ui/badge
- Urgency copy (top-right, muted text-sm):
    BAD   → 'Use immediately'
    OLD   → 'Going bad soon'
    FRESH → 'Expires in {N} days' (use getDaysUntilExpiration)
- Item name: text-2xl font-bold in card body
- Item type name (from item.itemTypes[0]?.name)
- Percent consumed: 'Currently {N}% consumed' — muted
- AtRiskReviewCardOverlay: rendered inside the card, receives dragX and SWIPE_THRESHOLD=80
- Action buttons (only when isTop=true):
    [🍽 Eaten] (green) [🗑 Discard] (red/destructive) side-by-side, full-width split
    Below those: [✏ Update details] toggle button (opens AtRiskReviewCardDetails)
- AtRiskReviewCardDetails: rendered below buttons inside AnimatePresence when showDetails=true

DEPENDS ON: broccoli-dashboard-479 (for ReviewDecision type), broccoli-dashboard-rqy (for AtRiskReviewCardOverlay)."}

{"description":"Build the directional action hint overlays that animate as the user drags a card. FILE: src/components/core/AtRiskReview/AtRiskReviewCardOverlay.tsx

IMPORTS NEEDED:
  import { motion, useTransform, type MotionValue } from 'framer-motion';
  import { Utensils, Trash2 } from 'lucide-react';

PROPS:
  interface AtRiskReviewCardOverlayProps {
    dragX: MotionValue<number>;
    threshold: number;  // SWIPE_THRESHOLD constant from parent card (80)
  }

IMPLEMENTATION:
Both overlays are absolutely positioned covering the full card face (inset-0 absolute pointer-events-none rounded-2xl). Use motion.div with a style={{ opacity }} driven by a useTransform — this means opacity updates happen without React re-renders, keeping drag performance smooth.

RIGHT overlay (Eaten — appears when dragging right):
  const eatOpacity = useTransform(dragX, [0, threshold], [0, 1]);
  className: 'absolute inset-0 rounded-2xl border-2 border-green-500/50 bg-green-500/20 dark:bg-green-400/20 flex items-center justify-center z-10 pointer-events-none'
  Content: <Utensils size={48} className='text-green-700 dark:text-green-300' /> + <span className='text-2xl font-bold text-green-700 dark:text-green-300 mt-2'>EATEN</span> (stacked vertically centered)

LEFT overlay (Discard — appears when dragging left):
  const discardOpacity = useTransform(dragX, [-threshold, 0], [1, 0]);
  className: 'absolute inset-0 rounded-2xl border-2 border-red-500/50 bg-red-500/20 dark:bg-red-400/20 flex items-center justify-center z-10 pointer-events-none'
  Content: <Trash2 size={48} className='text-red-700 dark:text-red-300' /> + <span className='text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 dark:text-red-300 mt-2'>DISCARD</span>

Both useTransform calls use the default clamp behaviour, so opacity stays at 0 below threshold and reaches 1 at exactly threshold — giving a clear visual signal that the swipe will commit.

NOTE: This component intentionally has no state and no side effects. It purely drives visual feedback from the parent card's MotionValue. Keep it that way.

DEPENDS ON: broccoli-dashboard-z4y passes dragX and SWIPE_THRESHOLD to this component. However this file can be authored first since it has no runtime dependency on the card — just the MotionValue type from framer-motion."}

{"description":"Build the expandable detail panel that slides open when the user taps 'Update details' on a card. FILE: src/components/core/AtRiskReview/AtRiskReviewCardDetails.tsx

IMPORTS NEEDED:
  import { useState } from 'react';
  import { motion, AnimatePresence } from 'framer-motion';
  import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button';
  import { ItemStatusType } from '@/generated/prisma/client';
  import type { CombinedItemType } from '@/components/core/Inventory';
  import type { ReviewDecision } from './useAtRiskReview';

PROPS:
  interface AtRiskReviewCardDetailsProps {
    item: CombinedItemType;
    onConfirm: (decision: { type: 'updated'; percentConsumed: number; status?: ItemStatusType }) => void;
    onCancel: () => void;
  }

LOCAL STATE:
  const [percentConsumed, setPercentConsumed] = useState(item.percentConsumed);
  const [statusOverride, setStatusOverride] = useState<ItemStatusType | undefined>(undefined);

ANIMATION: This component is rendered inside AnimatePresence in the parent AtRiskReviewCard. Wrap content in:
  <motion.div
    initial={{ height: 0, opacity: 0 }}
    animate={{ height: 'auto', opacity: 1 }}
    exit={{ height: 0, opacity: 0 }}
    transition={{ type: 'spring', bounce: 0.1, duration: 0.4 }}
    className='overflow-hidden'
  >

UI LAYOUT (mirrors ItemForm.tsx patterns — use same spacing and Tailwind classes):
1. Large percentage display:
   <p className='text-center text-5xl font-bold tabular-nums'>{percentConsumed}%</p>

2. Native range slider (full-width, below the number):
   <input
     type='range' min={0} max={100} value={percentConsumed}
     onChange={e => setPercentConsumed(Number(e.target.value))}
     className='w-full accent-primary'
   />

3. Quick-pick buttons grid (5 columns, evenly spaced):
   [0%] [25%] [50%] [75%] [100%]
   Each is a Button — variant='default' when value matches current percentConsumed, otherwise variant='outline'.
   Clicking a quick-pick also updates setPercentConsumed.
   Smart default: if percentConsumed reaches 100, also call setStatusOverride(ItemStatusType.EATEN).

4. Status action row (3 buttons, full-width, side-by-side):
   [🍽 Still eating]  [✅ All eaten]  [🗑 Threw it out]
   - 'Still eating': setStatusOverride(undefined) — keeps item's current status, only updates %
   - 'All eaten': setStatusOverride(ItemStatusType.EATEN); setPercentConsumed(100)
   - 'Threw it out': setStatusOverride(ItemStatusType.DISCARDED)
   Highlight the active choice with variant='default', others variant='outline'.
   When statusOverride is DISCARDED, grey out (opacity-50) the percent slider and quick-pick buttons — % is irrelevant.

5. Confirm button:
   <Button className='w-full bg-green-600 hover:bg-green-700 text-white' onClick={handleConfirm}>
     Save & Next →
   </Button>
   handleConfirm calls: onConfirm({ type: 'updated', percentConsumed, status: statusOverride })

6. Cancel link:
   <button className='text-sm text-muted-foreground underline' onClick={onCancel}>Never mind</button>

NOTE: onCancel collapses the panel (parent sets showDetails=false). onConfirm calls advance() in useAtRiskReview via onDecision in AtRiskReviewCard, which pops the queue and fires the updateItem mutation.

DEPENDS ON: broccoli-dashboard-479 (for ReviewDecision type exported from useAtRiskReview.ts)."}

{"description":"Build the deck component that renders the stacked card queue. FILE: src/components/core/AtRiskReview/AtRiskReviewDeck.tsx

IMPORTS NEEDED:
  import { AnimatePresence, motion } from 'framer-motion';
  import { useEffect, useRef, useState } from 'react';
  import { AtRiskReviewCard } from './AtRiskReviewCard';
  import type { CombinedItemType } from '@/components/core/Inventory';
  import type { ReviewDecision } from './useAtRiskReview';
  import { Swipe } from 'lucide-react'; // or a custom SVG hint

PROPS:
  interface AtRiskReviewDeckProps {
    queue: CombinedItemType[];
    onDecision: (itemId: number, decision: ReviewDecision) => void;
    isLoading?: boolean;
  }

STACKING LAYOUT:
Render the top 3 cards from queue simultaneously (or fewer if queue.length < 3). Each card is wrapped in a motion.div that is absolutely positioned. The container needs position: relative with min-h-[520px] to reserve enough vertical space.

Per-depth positioning (index 0 = top/front card):
  index 0: scale=1.00, y=0px,  zIndex=3, isTop=true
  index 1: scale=0.96, y=8px,  zIndex=2, isTop=false
  index 2: scale=0.92, y=16px, zIndex=1, isTop=false

Each wrapper motion.div gets: animate={{ scale, y, zIndex }} transition={{ type: 'spring', stiffness: 300, damping: 30 }}
This means when the top card is removed (after onDecision), the remaining cards automatically animate into their new depth positions.

ANIMATEPRESENCE:
  <AnimatePresence mode='popLayout'>
    {queue.slice(0, 3).map((item, index) => (
      <motion.div
        key={item.id}
        className='absolute w-full'
        animate={{ scale: [1, 0.96, 0.92][index], y: [0, 8, 16][index], zIndex: [3, 2, 1][index] }}
        transition={{ type: 'spring', stiffness: 300, damping: 30 }}
      >
        <AtRiskReviewCard
          item={item}
          isTop={index === 0}
          onDecision={(decision) => onDecision(item.id, decision)}
        />
      </motion.div>
    ))}
  </AnimatePresence>

EMPTY STATE: When queue.length === 0 and !isLoading, render null (parent AtRiskReviewModal switches to AtRiskReviewComplete screen).

SKELETON STATE: When isLoading=true, render a single placeholder:
  <div className='rounded-2xl animate-pulse bg-muted min-h-[400px] w-full max-w-sm mx-auto' />

SWIPE HINT: On first render, show a subtle animated hint after a 2-second delay. The hint is a small arrow icon that tweens left and right. Dismiss it (set to null) once ANY swipe decision is detected.
  - localStorage key: 'broccoli:atRiskReview:hintSeen'
  - On mount, if localStorage does NOT have this key, set a 2-second timeout to show the hint
  - Once any onDecision fires with type !== 'skipped' (first actual swipe), set localStorage key and dismiss hint
  - The hint renders as an absolutely-positioned overlay at the bottom-center of the deck, below the top card, so it does not interfere with dragging

DEPENDS ON: broccoli-dashboard-z4y (AtRiskReviewCard). Build alongside broccoli-dashboard-n5z (AtRiskReviewModal)."}

{"description":"Build the top-level modal shell. FILE: src/components/core/AtRiskReview/AtRiskReviewModal.tsx

IMPORTS NEEDED:
  import { useEffect } from 'react';
  import { useQueryState } from 'nuqs';
  import { useRouter } from 'next/navigation';
  import { Progress } from '@/components/ui/progress';
  import { BottomDrawer } from '@/components/BottomDrawer';
  import { useMediaQueries } from '@/context/MediaQueriesContext';
  import { X } from 'lucide-react';
  import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button';
  import { useAtRiskReview } from './useAtRiskReview';
  import { useAtRiskReviewSession } from './useAtRiskReviewSession';
  import { AtRiskReviewDeck } from './AtRiskReviewDeck';
  import { AtRiskReviewComplete } from './AtRiskReviewComplete';

GATE LOGIC (render null if any condition fails):
  const { isMobile } = useMediaQueries();
  const session = useAtRiskReviewSession();
  const review = useAtRiskReview();

  const shouldOpen = isMobile && (session.shouldShow) && (review.isLoading || !review.isEmpty);
  if (!shouldOpen) return null;

Note: include review.isLoading in the gate check so the modal opens immediately (showing skeleton) rather than waiting for data to load.

VAUL DRAWER USAGE:
Use the existing BottomDrawer component (src/components/BottomDrawer.tsx). Key props:
  - open={isOpen} — manage with useState(shouldOpen) initialised on mount
  - onOpenChange={setIsOpen}
  - renderHeader={null}  — completely suppress the default header (we render a custom one)
  - classNames={{ content: 'h-[100dvh] max-h-[100dvh]' }}  — full-height on mobile

Inside the drawer, render:
  1. Custom drag handle: <div className='mx-auto mb-4 h-1.5 w-12 rounded-full bg-zinc-300 dark:bg-zinc-700 mt-3' />
  2. Custom header row:
     - Left: <h2>'Kitchen check-in'</h2> + <p>'{N} items need attention'</p>
     - Right: X button with tooltip 'Remind me later' — closes modal WITHOUT marking session complete (user sees it again next time)
  3. 'Don't show today' link — closes AND calls session.markComplete()
  4. Progress bar:
     const reviewed = review.results.length;
     const total = review.queue.length + reviewed;
     const percent = total > 0 ? Math.round((reviewed / total) * 100) : 0;
     <Progress value={percent} className='h-1 my-2' />
     (Progress is from @radix-ui/react-progress, already installed — import from '@/components/ui/progress')
  5. Body — conditionally:
     - If review.isEmpty && review.results.length > 0: render <AtRiskReviewComplete results={review.results} onClose={() => { session.markComplete(); setIsOpen(false); }} />
     - Otherwise: render <AtRiskReviewDeck queue={review.queue} onDecision={review.advance} isLoading={review.isLoading} />

PUSH NOTIFICATION DEEP-LINK HANDLING:
  1. nuqs intent param:
     const [intent, setIntent] = useQueryState('intent');
     useEffect(() => {
       if (intent === 'review') {
         session.setForceOpen(true);
         setIsOpen(true);
         void setIntent(null);  // clear the param
       }
     }, [intent]);

  2. Service worker postMessage listener:
     useEffect(() => {
       if (!navigator.serviceWorker) return;
       const handler = (event: MessageEvent) => {
         if (event.data?.type === 'OPEN_AT_RISK_REVIEW') {
           session.setForceOpen(true);
           setIsOpen(true);
         }
       };
       navigator.serviceWorker.addEventListener('message', handler);
       return () => navigator.serviceWorker.removeEventListener('message', handler);
     }, []);

ACCESSIBILITY:
  - The BottomDrawer renders a hidden Drawer.Title via Vaul. Pass title='Kitchen check-in: review at-risk items' to BottomDrawer even if visually suppressed.
  - When the modal opens, focus the first Button in the top card (use autoFocus on the Eaten button in AtRiskReviewCard when isTop=true).
  - When modal closes, return focus to document.activeElement saved before open.

DEPENDS ON: broccoli-dashboard-8d4 (AtRiskReviewDeck), broccoli-dashboard-ehp (AtRiskReviewComplete)."}

{"description":"Build the completion screen shown when all cards in the deck have been actioned. FILE: src/components/core/AtRiskReview/AtRiskReviewComplete.tsx

IMPORTS NEEDED:
  import { useEffect } from 'react';
  import { motion } from 'framer-motion';
  import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button';
  import type { ReviewResult } from './useAtRiskReview';
  import { ItemStatusType } from '@/generated/prisma/client';

PROPS:
  interface AtRiskReviewCompleteProps {
    results: ReviewResult[];
    onClose: () => void;
  }

DERIVED VALUES (computed from results, memoize with useMemo):
  const eatenCount    = results.filter(r => r.decision.type === 'eaten' || (r.decision.type === 'updated' && (r.decision.status === ItemStatusType.EATEN || r.decision.percentConsumed === 100))).length;
  const discardedCount = results.filter(r => r.decision.type === 'discarded' || (r.decision.type === 'updated' && r.decision.status === ItemStatusType.DISCARDED)).length;
  const updatedCount  = results.filter(r => r.decision.type === 'updated' && r.decision.status !== ItemStatusType.EATEN && r.decision.status !== ItemStatusType.DISCARDED).length;
  const skippedCount  = results.filter(r => r.decision.type === 'skipped').length;

CONFETTI (fires once on mount, only if eatenCount > 0):
  useEffect(() => {
    if (eatenCount > 0) {
      void import('canvas-confetti').then(({ default: confetti }) => {
        confetti({
          particleCount: 80,
          spread: 60,
          origin: { y: 0.6 },
          colors: ['#85c941', '#4ade80', '#22c55e'],  // app brand green + greens
        });
      });
    }
  }, []); // empty deps — intentionally fires once on mount

HEADLINE LOGIC:
  const allActioned = skippedCount === 0;
  const headline = eatenCount > 0 && discardedCount === 0 && skippedCount === 0
    ? 'Kitchen is spotless! 🎉'
    : eatenCount > 0 || discardedCount > 0
    ? 'Nice work checking in! 🥦'
    : 'No worries, check back tomorrow.';

VISUAL LAYOUT (centered, full height of the drawer body):
  Wrap in: <motion.div initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 20 }} animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }} transition={{ duration: 0.4 }} className='flex flex-col items-center justify-center h-full gap-6 text-center px-4'>

  1. Large emoji: {eatenCount > 0 ? '🥦' : '✨'} — text-6xl
  2. Headline: {headline} — text-2xl font-bold
  3. Sub-headline: 'Your inventory is up to date.' — text-muted-foreground
  4. Stats row (horizontal flex, wrap, only show non-zero counts):
     {eatenCount > 0    && <StatBadge emoji='🍽'  label={} />}
